reviewText: Very interesting interviews with Delerue, and other material on his life in music which was primarily for film. However, there's not much of his music itself on this DVD, so depending on your interests this disk might be a 5 for you, or less.
As the crowned prince of lush, evocative, and sensitive film scores, Delerue here gets at least SOME of his due. I only wish the film had been twice as long!
